[normal] As is done in relation to the abstract review procedure in the Irish Constitution: see Article 26 (which describes the procedure) and Article 34.3.3 (which provides that the validity of a statute that has passed the Article 26 procedure cannot be further challenged).
[normal] As applies in relation to the New Zealand Bill of Rights Act 1990 (section 7).
